gov.anl.ipns.ViewTools.Components.Transparency
Class Note

java.lang.Object
  gov.anl.ipns.ViewTools.Components.Transparency.Note
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public class Note
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable

This class creates a datastructure to easily group together a String annotation, its location to be displayed, and the bounds it was created in. This class is primarily used by the AnnotationOverlay.

See Also:
AnnotationOverlay, Serialized Form

Note

public Note(java.lang.String t,
            Line l,
            floatPoint2D wc_p1,
            floatPoint2D wc_p2)
This constructor creates a Note object with bottom-left corner at point p2 in pixel coordinates and wc_p2 in world coordinates.

Parameters:
t - - the actual text message
l - - the line from point of interest to the annotation (in pixel coordinates)
wc_p1 - - the world coordinate value of p1 of the line.
wc_p2 - - the world coordinate value of p2 of the line.

public Line getLine()
Get the Line object that was created along with this annotation.

Returns:
